alwaysFrom.name: alwaysFrom
alwaysFrom.short_desc: Set the global from address and name.

alwaysReplyTo.name: alwaysReplyTo
alwaysReplyTo.short_desc: Set the global reply-to address and name.

alwaysTo.name: alwaysTo
alwaysTo.short_desc: Set the global to address and name.

to.name: to
to.short_desc: Begin the process of mailing a mailable class instance.

cc.name: cc
cc.short_desc: Begin the process of mailing a mailable class instance.

bcc.name: bcc
bcc.short_desc: Begin the process of mailing a mailable class instance.

html.name: html
html.short_desc: Send a new message with only an HTML part.

raw.name: raw
raw.short_desc: Send a new message with only a raw text part.

plain.name: plain
plain.short_desc: Send a new message with only a plain part.

render.name: render
render.short_desc: Render the given message as a view.

send.name: send
send.short_desc: Send a new message using a view.

queue.name: queue
queue.short_desc: Queue a new e-mail message for sending.

onQueue.name: onQueue
onQueue.short_desc: Queue a new e-mail message for sending on the given queue.

queueOn.name: queueOn
queueOn.short_desc: Queue a new e-mail message for sending on the given queue.
queueOn.long_desc: This method didn't match rest of framework's "onQueue" phrasing. Added "onQueue".

later.name: later
later.short_desc: Queue a new e-mail message for sending after (n) seconds.

laterOn.name: laterOn
laterOn.short_desc: Queue a new e-mail message for sending after (n) seconds on the given queue.

failures.name: failures
failures.short_desc: Get the array of failed recipients.

mixin.name: mixin
mixin.short_desc: Mix another object into the class.

assertSent.name: assertSent
assertSent.short_desc: Assert if a mailable was sent based on a truth-test callback.

assertNotSent.name: assertNotSent
assertNotSent.short_desc: Determine if a mailable was not sent based on a truth-test callback.

assertNothingSent.name: assertNothingSent
assertNothingSent.short_desc: Assert that no mailables were sent.

assertQueued.name: assertQueued
assertQueued.short_desc: Assert if a mailable was queued based on a truth-test callback.

assertNotQueued.name: assertNotQueued
assertNotQueued.short_desc: Determine if a mailable was not queued based on a truth-test callback.

assertNothingQueued.name: assertNothingQueued
assertNothingQueued.short_desc: Assert that no mailables were queued.

sent.name: sent
sent.short_desc: Get all of the mailables matching a truth-test callback.

hasSent.name: hasSent
hasSent.short_desc: Determine if the given mailable has been sent.

queued.name: queued
queued.short_desc: Get all of the queued mailables matching a truth-test callback.

hasQueued.name: hasQueued
hasQueued.short_desc: Determine if the given mailable has been queued.
